    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-06T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-06T13:00:00-05:00" n="840"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d840">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 701.6232/10</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MEV1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-06T13:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 6, 1917, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your June 5, 11 a.m. Ambassador at Buenos Aires has issued safe-conduct to
                    following: <persName>Pauli</persName> and Danner, valet; Willdolt, attaché;
                    Grunon, chancellor; Munzenthaler, Consul General; Steinfiegel and Pfaff,
                    consuls; Markmann, secretary and wife.</p>
                <p>You may issue following safe-conduct to balance of official party embarking at
                    Rio de Janeiro. Also similar safe-conduct may be issued to late German Minister
                    to Bolivia.</p>
                <p>[Here follows form of safe-conduct printed in telegram of June 2 to the
                    Ambassador in Argentine, above.]</p>
                <pb facs="0781" n="609" xml:id="pg_609"/>
                <p>The right of search is reserved by the United States authorities.</p>
                <p>Please inform Department for what reason <hi rend="italic">Frisia</hi> is
                    touching at New York <hi rend="italic">en route</hi> to Halifax and how long she
                    is expected to stay New York.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
